equences."},"89":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-1","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/approvals#kinds","content":"Kinds"},"90":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-2","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/approvals#the-ask-contract","content":"The ask contract"},"91":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-3","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/approvals#status-and-resolution","content":"Status and resolution"},"92":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-4","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/approvals#timed-approvals-with-fallback","content":"Timed approvals with fallback"},"93":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-5","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/approvals#per-kind-consequences","content":"Per-kind consequences"},"94":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-6","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/approvals#api--mcp","content":"API & MCP"},"95":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-7","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals","content":"An **approval** is a declared question with a declared consequence, presented to a human as a card in the web app, over Telegram, or through the API/MCP. Cards can hold a run before it executes (`waiting_approval`), pause a workflow mid-run at an engine gate, or simply record a decision. A run held on an approval waits indefinitely — waiting never fails it."},"96":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-8","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#kinds","content":"Kind"},"97":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-9","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#kinds","content":"What it represents"},"98":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-10","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#kinds","content":"`workflow_gate`"},"99":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-11","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#kinds","content":"A workflow paused at a gate; the decision releases or denies that step."},"100":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-12","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#kinds","content":"`escalation`"},"101":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-13","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#kinds","content":"Autonomous recovery gave up; a human records how to proceed."},"102":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-14","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#kinds","content":"`side_effect`"},"103":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-15","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#kinds","content":"A gated side effect asking permission before it runs."},"104":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-16","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#kinds","content":"`custom`"},"105":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-17","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#kinds","content":"Any ad-hoc approval raised via the API."},"106":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-18","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#the-ask-contract","content":"The creator of a card states the ask up front, and every surface renders it verbatim:"},"107":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-19","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#the-ask-contract","content":"`action` — what exactly happens on approve."},"108":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-20","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#the-ask-contract","content":"`reason` — why a human is needed."},"109":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-21","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#the-ask-contract","content":"`audience` — who is asked: `operators` (default) or `admins`."},"110":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-22","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#the-ask-contract","content":"`options` — optional named choices (up to 8)."},"111":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-23","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#the-ask-contract","content":"An ask without both `action` and `reason` is treated as absent; such cards fall back to a heuristic ask explicitly marked `derived: true`, so a guessed question is never presented as an authored one."},"112":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-24","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#status-and-resolution","content":"A card's `status` is only ever `pending` or `resolved`. What was decided and by what live in separate fields:"},"113":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-25","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#status-and-resolution","content":"Field"},"114":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-26","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#status-and-resolution","content":"Values"},"115":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-27","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#status-and-resolution","content":"`resolution`"},"116":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-28","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#status-and-resolution","content":"`approved`, `rejected`, `changes_requested`, `superseded` (the run ended first), or `option:<id>`"},"117":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-29","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#status-and-resolution","content":"`resolvedVia`"},"118":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-30","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#status-and-resolution","content":"`human`, `fallback_timer` (autopilot), `engine` (decided on the runner), `policy` (auto-approved by policy), `system`"},"119":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-31","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#timed-approvals-with-fallback","content":"By default a card is blocking: nothing happens until someone decides. Supplying `timeoutMs` or `timeoutAt` at creation makes it a **timed approval**:"},"120":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-32","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#timed-approvals-with-fallback","content":"With a `fallback` decision (`approve` or `reject`), the configured decision is applied automatically when the timer elapses, recorded with `resolvedVia: \"fallback_timer\"`."},"121":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-33","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#timed-approvals-with-fallback","content":"Without a fallback, the elapsed card is flagged `fallback_required` and keeps waiting — no decision is invented, and the linked run is never failed by an elapsed timer."},"122":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-34","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#per-kind-consequences","content":"Every card answers \"what will my decision do\" honestly, computed from what resolving actually performs:"},"123":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-35","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#per-kind-consequences","content":"**`workflow_gate`** — approving a card holding a `waiting_approval` run releases it; approving a mid-run gate applies the decision to the paused workflow on the runner, which resumes past the gate. Reject/changes-requested cancel a held run, or take the workflow's own deny path mid-run."},"124":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-36","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#per-kind-consequences","content":"**`escalation`** — the run already ended: any decision records the call but does not restart the run (re-run it from the run page)."},"125":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-37","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#per-kind-consequences","content":"**`side_effect`** — approve allows the gated side effect; reject or changes-requested skip it. The run's completed work is unchanged either way."},"126":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-38","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#per-kind-consequences","content":"**`custom`** — approving a held run releases it to the queue; reject/changes-requested cancel it. On a card without a held run, the decision is simply recorded."},"127":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-39","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#per-kind-consequences","content":"The API exposes these as `whatHappensIfApproved` / `whatHappensIfRejected` / `whatHappensIfChangesRequested` / `whatHappensIfIgnored` in each card's `context`, alongside the ask, the linked run, and deep links."},"128":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-40","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#api--mcp","content":"Endpoint"},"129":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-41","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#api--mcp","content":"MCP tool"},"130":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-42","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#api--mcp","content":"Notes"},"131":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-43","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/approvals`"},"132":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-44","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#api--mcp","content":"`list_approvals`, `list_pending_approvals`"},"133":{"id":"/concepts/approvals-45","page_id":"/concepts/approvals","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/approvals#api--mcp","content":"`?status=pending\\|resolved`."},