:"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"`admin`"},"539":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-23","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"Everything. `admin` is a **superscope**: it satisfies every scope requirement, and admin-only endpoints (tokens, secrets, catalog edits, schedules, hooks, audit) require it."},"540":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-24","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"Reads such as listing runs, workflows, runners, or schedules need only an authenticated token, whatever its scopes. Runner lifecycle endpoints additionally enforce **run ownership**: only the runner token that claimed a run (or an admin) may report on it."},"541":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-25","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"`GET /api/tokens/scopes` (admin; MCP tool `list_token_scopes`) describes the scope vocabulary and the named presets the Tokens page offers:"},"542":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-26","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Preset"},"543":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-27","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Scopes"},"544":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-28","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Use for"},"545":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-29","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"**Everything** (default)"},"546":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-30","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"`api`, `mcp`, `approvals`"},"547":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-31","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"A normal person or agent: read everything, run workflows, decide approvals. No admin or runner rights."},"548":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-32","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"**Read-only**"},"549":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-33","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"`read`"},"550":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-34","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Dashboards, monitors, and cautious integrations that must never change state."},"551":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-35","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"**Approvals only**"},"552":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-36","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"`approvals`"},"553":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-37","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Approval inboxes and bots that only decide."},"554":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-38","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"**Runner**"},"555":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-39","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"`runner`"},"556":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-40","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Runner machines. Keep separate from human tokens."},"557":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-41","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"**Admin**"},"558":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-42","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"`admin`"},"559":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-43","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Full control, including tokens and secrets. Issue sparingly."},"560":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-44","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Finer-grained per-group write scopes (e.g. a token that can manage schedules but not run workflows) are a documented follow-up; today `api`/`mcp` grant the whole operating surface."},"561":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-45","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#bootstrap-token","content":"On first boot, if no access tokens exist, the Hub creates a `bootstrap-admin` token with the `admin`, `api`, `runner`, and `mcp` scopes and writes it to `data/bootstrap-token.txt` on the server (relative to the Hub's data directory). Use it to log in and mint narrower tokens, one per client or integration."},"562":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-46","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#browser-sessions","content":"The web app is an ordinary API client. `POST /api/auth/token-login` exchanges an access token for a **session cookie** — a signed copy of the token — so the browser session carries *exactly* the token's scopes, no extra power. Admin sections of the web app appear only for admin-scoped sessions. `POST /api/auth/logout` clears the cookie."},"563":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-47","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#telegram-webapp-sessions","content":"Approving from Telegram uses `POST /api/auth/telegram-webapp&#x60;, which verifies Telegram's signed init data against the configured bot and allowlisted users, then issues a session scoped to **`approvals` only** — narrower than any token session. A Telegram session can list and resolve approval cards but cannot start runs or touch admin surfaces."},"564":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-48","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Endpoint"},"565":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-49","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"MCP tool"},"566":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-50","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Notes"},"567":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-51","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/me`"},"568":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-52","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`whoami`"},"569":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-53","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Token name and scopes."},"570":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-54","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/tokens`"},"571":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-55","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`list_tokens`"},"572":{"id":"