rl":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"Workflow packages"},"1130":{"id":"/guides/mcp-48","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"`export_workflow_package`†, `validate_workflow_package`†, `preview_workflow_import`†, `import_workflow_package`†"},"1131":{"id":"/guides/mcp-49","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"Catalog"},"1132":{"id":"/guides/mcp-50","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"`list_agents`, `list_skills`, `search_knowledge`, `create_agent`†, `update_agent`†, `create_skill`†, `update_skill`†, `create_knowledge`†, `update_knowledge`†"},"1133":{"id":"/guides/mcp-51","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"Admin & updates"},"1134":{"id":"/guides/mcp-52","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"`get_audit_log`†, `list_alerts`†, `get_update_status`†, `apply_update`†"},"1135":{"id":"/guides/mcp-53","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"Assistant"},"1136":{"id":"/guides/mcp-54","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"`get_assistant_status`, `ask_assistant`"},"1137":{"id":"/guides/mcp-55","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"Tools marked † require an admin-scoped token."},"1138":{"id":"/guides/mcp-56","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"Workflow source is always created and edited **through these tools** —\n`create_workflow` / `update_workflow` take inline source bytes or an existing\n`workflow.bundleId`, and `import_workflow_package` installs a portable package\nas a disabled workflow. Bare file paths on the runner are rejected."},"1139":{"id":"/guides/mcp-57","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-parity-guarantee","content":"The tool list, the HTTP routes, and `/openapi.json` are all generated from one\nregistry, and a test fails the build when they drift: **every Hub API operation\nis either exposed as an MCP tool or carries a documented exemption** (exempt\noperations are browser pages, install assets, the runner-to-Hub machine\nprotocol, SSE streams that tools cover by polling, and legacy aliases). If you\ncan do it in the web UI or over HTTP, your agent can do it over MCP."},"1140":{"id":"/guides/mcp-58","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#recommended-agent-flow","content":"**`get_menu`** — orient: catalog, execution modes, follow-up paths."},"1141":{"id":"/guides/mcp-59","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#recommended-agent-flow","content":"**`preflight_workflow`** — dry-run your input; resolve `needs_input`\nquestions and `blocked` blockers before creating anything (or use\n`run_workflow` with `negotiate: true`, or the run-draft tools for a\nmulti-turn negotiation)."},"1142":{"id":"/guides/mcp-60","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#recommended-agent-flow","content":"**`run_workflow`** — include a short human-readable `input.title` so run\nlists and approval cards read well; choose `executionMode` `local` or\n`remote`."},"1143":{"id":"/guides/mcp-61","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#recommended-agent-flow","content":"**`get_run_timeline`** — poll with the returned `nextSince` cursor to page\nforward; drop to `get_run_logs` / `get_run_diagnostics` when something looks\nwrong, and fetch results with `get_run_artifacts` + `download_artifact`."},"1144":{"id":"/guides/mcp-62","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#recommended-agent-flow","content":"If a run pauses for a human, `list_pending_approvals` shows the card and\n`approve_run` / `reject_run` / `request_changes_run` resolve it (by\n`approvalId`, not `runId`)."},"1145":{"id":"/guides/releases","page_id":"/guides/releases","type":"page","content":"Versioning and releases","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Guides"],"tags":[],"url":"/guides/releases"},"1146":{"id":"/guides/releases-0","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases","content":"How Runyard itself is versioned, gated, released, and self-updated — and how the docs track each release."},"1147":{"id":"/guides/releases-1","page_id":"/guides/releases","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"CI pipeline"},"1148":{"id":"/guides/releases-2","page_id":"/guides/releases","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/releases#the-release-train-helper","content":"The release-train helper"},"1149":{"id":"/guides/releases-3","page_id":"/guides/releases","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/releases#self-update-for-deployments","content":"Self-update for deployments"},"1150":{"id":"/guides/releases-4","page_id":"/guides/releases","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/releases#docs-stay-current","content":"Docs stay current"},"1151":{"id":"/guides/releases-5","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases","content":"Runyard releases are semver git tags (`vX.Y.Z`). The version in `package.json` is the single source of truth and flows to `/api/version`, the OpenAPI document, the CLI, and the update checker."},"1152":{"id":"/guides/releases-6","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"The GitHub Actions pipeline (`.github/workflows/release.yml` and `images.yml`) has four jobs:"},"1153":{"id":"/guides/releases-7","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"Job"},"1154":{"id":"/guides/releases-8","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"Trigger"},"1155":{"id":"/guides/releases-9","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"What it does"},"1156":{"id":"/guides/releases-10","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"`test`"},"1157":{"id":"/guides/releases-11","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"Every PR and push to `main` (and tags)"},"1158":{"id":"/guides/releases-12","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"`pnpm test` + `pnpm build` on Node 22."},"1159":{"id":"/guides/releases-13","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"`sandbox-smoke`"},"1160":{"id":"/guides/releases-14","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"Same"},"1161":{"id":"/guides/releases-15","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"Real bubblewrap + AppArmor gate on Ubuntu 24.04: installs bwrap, loads the repo's AppArmor profile via the same script operators run, then runs the sandbox suites with `RUNYARD_REQUIRE_BWRAP=1` so the smoke test fails rather than skips."},"1162":{"id":"/guides/releases-16","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"`release`"},"1163":{"id":"/guides/releases-17","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"Pushed `v*` tags"},"1164":{"id":"/guides/releases-18","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"Publishes the GitHub Release with generated notes — only after `test` and `sandbox-smoke` are green. A red run never publishes."},"1165":{"id":"/guides/releases-19","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"`build-push` (images)"},"1166":{"id":"/guides/releases-20","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"Pushed `v*` tags"},"1167":{"id":"/guides/releases-21","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#ci-pipeline","content":"Builds and pushes GHCR `hub` and `runner` container images behind the same two gates, and records both image digests as a release artifact."},"1168":{"id":"/guides/releases-22","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#the-release-train-helper","content":"`scripts/release-train.mjs` gives operators (and the deployment watchdog) machine-readable release state:"},"1169":{"id":"/guides/releases-23","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#the-release-train-helper","content":"Local gates are `test`, `build`, and `diff-check` (`git diff --check`); `sandbox-smoke` only runs on a real Actions kernel, so its evidence is recorded by hand from a green CI run. Evidence is keyed to the full HEAD SHA in `data/release-evidence.json`, so a green gate can never be inherited across new commits, and `status` tells you the next action (run a gate, fix a failure, tag)."},"1170":{"id":"/guides/releases-24","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#self-update-for-deployments","content":"A deployed Hub checks the public GitHub Releases API passively (outbound-only, `UPDATE_CHECK_ENABLED`, default on) and shows admins an update badge."},"1171":{"id":"/guides/releases-25","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#self-update-for-deployments","content":"Surface"},"1172":{"id":"/guides/releases-26","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#self-update-for-deployments","content":"Operation"},"1173":{"id":"/guides/releases-27","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#self-update-for-deployments","content":"HTTP"},"1174":{"id":"/guides/releases-28","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#self-update-for-deployments","content":"`GET /api/update-status` (admin) — is a newer release available, current update state."},"1175":{"id":"/guides/releases-29","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#self-update-for-deployments","content":"HTTP"},"1176":{"id":"/guides/releases-30","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#self-update-for-deployments","content":"`POST /api/update/apply` (admin) — apply the update over HTTP; disabled unless `UPDATE_APPLY_ENABLED=1`."},"1177":{"id":"/guides/releases-31","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#self-update-for-deployments","content":"MCP"},"1178":{"id":"/guides/releases-32","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#self-update-for-deployments","content":"`get_update_status`, `apply_update`."},"1179":{"id":"/guides/releases-33","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#self-update-for-deployments","content":"CLI"},"1180":{"id":"/guides/releases-34","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#self-update-for-deployments","content":"`runyard update [tag]` on the host — the recommended path."},"1181":{"id":"/guides/releases-35","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#self-update-for-deployments","content":"`runyard update` drains runners (bounded grace window; it aborts rather than kill in-flight runs), swaps the checkout to the new tag, restarts services, verifies health, and rolls back automatically on failure. The data directory (database, secrets, artifacts) survives every update and rollback."},"1182":{"id":"/guides/releases-36","page_id":"/guides/releases","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/releases#docs-stay-current","content":"Runyard ships a repo-agnostic `docs-update` workflow that keeps documentation honest against each release. When a release is published, a GitHub Actions step triggers it on the project's own Hub through an authenticated workflow endpoint (`release-docs-update`); the workflow inspects only the git diff between the previous and new release tags — never the whole repository — and reports proposed documentation updates. In its opt-in `apply` mode it edits docs in an isolated worktree branch instead, and that branch reaches the target branch only through a human-approved run promotion. The repository, docs path, docs framework, and file-selection rules are all workflow inputs, so any repo can adopt it."},"1183":{"id":"/guides/security","page_id":"/guides/security","type":"page","content":"Security model","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Guides"],"tags":[],"url":"/guides/security"},"1184":{"id":"/guides/security-0","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security","content":"Trust boundary, token scopes, secrets handling, runner sandboxing, and production posture for a Runyard deployment."},"1185":{"id":"/guides/security-1","page_id":"/guides/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"Trust boundary"},"1186":{"id":"/guides/security-2","page_id":"/guides/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"Scopes"},"1187":{"id":"/guides/security-3","page_id":"/guides/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/security#secrets","content":"Secrets"},"1188":{"id":"/guides/security-4","page_id":"/guides/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/security#workflow-endpoints","content":"Workflow endpoints"},"1189":{"id":"/guides/security-5","page_id":"/guides/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/security#approval-gating","content":"Approval gating"},"1190":{"id":"/guides/security-6","page_id":"/guides/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/security#runner-sandboxing","content":"Runner sandboxing"},"1191":{"id":"/guides/security-7","page_id":"/guides/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/security#production-posture","content":"Production posture"},"1192":{"id":"/guides/security-8","page_id":"/guides/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/security#what-stays-out-of-public-discovery-docs","content":"What stays out of public discovery docs"},"1193":{"id":"/guides/security-9","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security","content":"Runyard is one private deployment per company, and the security model follows from that: a small, deliberate unauthenticated surface; scoped bearer tokens for everything else; secrets encrypted at rest and never echoed; and approval gates in front of dangerous work."},"1194":{"id":"/guides/security-10","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"Every operation requires either a bearer access token (`Authorization: Bearer ...`) or a browser session created by exchanging such a token — and the session carries exactly the token's scopes, no extra power. The unauthenticated surface is deliberately tiny:"},"1195":{"id":"/guides/security-11","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"Endpoint"},"1196":{"id":"/guides/security-12","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"Purpose"},"1197":{"id":"/guides/security-13","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"`/healthz`, `/readyz`"},"1198":{"id":"/guides/security-14","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"Liveness/readiness probes."},"1199":{"id":"/guides/security-15","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"`/api/version`, `/version`"},"1200":{"id":"/guides/security-16","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"Product name and version."},"1201":{"id":"/guides/security-17","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"`/`, `/app`, `/docs`"},"1202":{"id":"/guides/security-18","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"Landing page, app shell, documentation pages (data still requires auth)."},"1203":{"id":"/guides/security-19","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"`/llms.txt`"},"1204":{"id":"/guides/security-20","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"Static, generic agent discovery document."},"1205":{"id":"/guides/security-21","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"`/openapi.json`"},"1206":{"id":"/guides/security-22","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"Generated API description."},"1207":{"id":"/guides/security-23","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"`/install.sh`, `/cli.tgz`"},"1208":{"id":"/guides/security-24","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"Client install assets."},"1209":{"id":"/guides/security-25","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#trust-boundary","content":"Two narrow exceptions authenticate by other means: `POST /api/telegram/webhook` is verified against the configured bot and webhook secret, and `POST /api/workflow-endpoints/{slug}` submissions authenticate with that endpoint's own secret (below). `GET /api/setup` returns only a reduced identity payload (instance name, auth mode) to unauthenticated callers."},"1210":{"id":"/guides/security-26","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"Tokens carry scopes; admins mint them from the Connect tab or `POST /api/tokens`."},"1211":{"id":"/guides/security-27","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"Scope"},"1212":{"id":"/guides/security-28","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"Grants"},"1213":{"id":"/guides/security-29","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"`api`"},"1214":{"id":"/guides/security-30","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"Run workflows and read runs over HTTP."},"1215":{"id":"/guides/security-31","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"`mcp`"},"1216":{"id":"/guides/security-32","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"The same operations over the MCP server."},"1217":{"id":"/guides/security-33","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"`runner`"},"1218":{"id":"/guides/security-34","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"The runner protocol: register, heartbeat, claim runs, report lifecycle."},"1219":{"id":"/guides/security-35","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"`approvals`"},"1220":{"id":"/guides/security-36","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"Create and resolve approval cards (the scope Telegram WebApp sessions get)."},"1221":{"id":"/guides/security-37","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"`admin`"},"1222":{"id":"/guides/security-38","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"Superscope: satisfies every scope requirement and gates all mutation of workflows, secrets, tokens, schedules, hooks, and updates."},"1223":{"id":"/guides/security-39","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#scopes","content":"Runner tokens are additionally subject to **run-ownership checks**: a run's lifecycle endpoints (`start`, `events`, `complete`, `fail`, artifact upload) only accept the runner that owns the run, or an admin. One compromised runner token cannot report on, or interfere with, another runner's work."},"1224":{"id":"/guides/security-40","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#secrets","content":"The reusable secret store is enabled by setting `SECRETS_ENC_KEY` (a 32-byte key) on the Hub; without a valid key the feature is disabled rather than degraded. Values are encrypted at rest and are write-only from the API's point of view: `GET /api/secrets` returns names and metadata, never values, and secrets are redacted from API responses, events, approval cards, and audit entries. Workflows reference secrets by name; the Hub injects values into runs that declared them."},"1225":{"id":"/guides/security-41","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#workflow-endpoints","content":"Fixed-purpose webhook-style intake (`POST /api/workflow-endpoints/{slug}`) is designed for exposure to semi-trusted callers: each endpoint has its **own** secret (not a Hub token), plus rate limits, payload size caps, and deduplication. An endpoint can only trigger the single workflow an admin configured it for — a leaked endpoint secret does not grant API access."},"1226":{"id":"/guides/security-42","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#approval-gating","content":"Workflows whose consequences warrant a human get an `approvalPolicy` that holds runs in `waiting_approval` until someone approves; mid-run engine gates and gated side effects (post-run hook profiles are admin-defined and admin-configured) use the same approval cards. See Approvals."},"1227":{"id":"/guides/security-43","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#runner-sandboxing","content":"Runners can execute workflow processes inside a bubblewrap sandbox (`RUNNER_SANDBOX=bubblewrap`), and the repo ships a narrow AppArmor profile (`deploy/apparmor/install.sh`) that grants unprivileged user-namespace creation to bwrap on Ubuntu 24.04+ kernels that restrict it. This is not on faith: CI runs a `sandbox-smoke` job on every push that installs bubblewrap, loads the profile through the same operator install script, and runs the sandbox suites with `RUNYARD_REQUIRE_BWRAP=1` so the real-bwrap smoke test fails instead of silently skipping if the path regresses."},"1228":{"id":"/guides/security-44","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#production-posture","content":"**TLS reverse proxy** — keep the Hub on `127.0.0.1` and terminate TLS in front (the installer prints a Caddy snippet); set `BASE_URL` to the https URL."},"1229":{"id":"/guides/security-45","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#production-posture","content":"**Session secret** — set `RUNYARD_HUB_SESSION_SECRET` explicitly in production (the installer generates one)."},"1230":{"id":"/guides/security-46","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#production-posture","content":"**`SECRETS_ENC_KEY`** — set it once and guard it; rotating the key makes previously stored secrets unreadable."},"1231":{"id":"/guides/security-47","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#production-posture","content":"**Token hygiene** — issue narrow scopes, set `expiresInDays` on tokens for humans, and revoke with `DELETE /api/tokens/{id}`; retire the bootstrap token once real admin tokens exist."},"1232":{"id":"/guides/security-48","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#production-posture","content":"**Audit log review** — every actor-attributable action lands in the audit log (`runyard audit`, `GET /api/audit`, `get_audit_log`)."},"1233":{"id":"/guides/security-49","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#production-posture","content":"**Updates** — leave `UPDATE_APPLY_ENABLED` off unless you want the admin-gated HTTP apply; prefer `runyard update` on the host. See Releases."},"1234":{"id":"/guides/security-50","page_id":"/guides/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/security#what-stays-out-of-public-discovery-docs","content":"`/llms.txt` and `/openapi.json` are static and generic by design: they describe the product and its surfaces, never your deployment. The live workflow catalog, runner details, secret names, and operator configuration are only available behind auth (`GET /api/menu`, `GET /api/workflows`). An unauthenticated crawler learns that a Runyard exists — not what yours can do."},"1235":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","type":"page","content":"Troubleshooting","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Guides"],"tags":[],"url":"/guides/troubleshooting"},"1236":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-0","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting","content":"Practical fixes for stuck runs, failure classes, preflight blockers, auth errors, and delivery problems."},"1237":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-1","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/troubleshooting#a-run-is-stuck-in-queued","content":"A run is stuck in `queued`"},"1238":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-2","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/troubleshooting#a-run-is-in-waiting_approval","content":"A run is in `waiting_approval`"},"1239":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-3","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Failure classes"},"1240":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-4","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/troubleshooting#preflight-blockers","content":"Preflight blockers"},"1241":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-5","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/troubleshooting#401--403-responses","content":"401 / 403 responses"},"1242":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-6","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/troubleshooting#secrets-not-configured","content":"Secrets not configured"},"1243":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-7","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/troubleshooting#telegram-not-delivering","content":"Telegram not delivering"},"1244":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-8","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/troubleshooting#runner-agent-auth-expired","content":"Runner agent auth expired"},"1245":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-9","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/troubleshooting#where-to-look-generally","content":"Where to look, generally"},"1246":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-10","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#a-run-is-stuck-in-queued","content":"A queued run means no runner has claimed it — either no runner is online, or none matches the run's required tags / requested location (`local` vs `vps`/`remote`)."},"1247":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-11","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#a-run-is-stuck-in-queued","content":"A runner is considered offline after \\~30 seconds without a heartbeat. If the runner should be online, check its service logs on the runner host:"},"1248":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-12","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#a-run-is-stuck-in-queued","content":"Common causes: the runner unit is idling because `RUNYARD_HUB_TOKEN` is empty or revoked; the runner's tags do not include what the workflow requires (`requiredRunnerTags`, for example `smithers`); or the run asked for `--where local` and only `vps` runners are registered. Running `runyard preflight <workflow>` before enqueueing catches `no_matching_runner` up front."},"1249":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-13","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#a-run-is-in-waiting_approval","content":"The run is held on an approval card, which is by design: approval-held runs are never failed or reaped for waiting. Find and resolve the card — web **Approvals**, `runyard approvals` then `runyard approve|reject|request-changes <approval-id>`, or the MCP tools. See Approvals."},"1250":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-14","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Terminal failures carry a class so you know whether to fix input, config, or infrastructure:"},"1251":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-15","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Class"},"1252":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-16","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Meaning"},"1253":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-17","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"What to do"},"1254":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-18","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"`blocked_by_gate`"},"1255":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-19","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"A quality gate (tests, lint, typecheck, build, eval) failed inside the workflow."},"1256":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-20","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Read the run logs for the gate output; fix the underlying work and re-run."},"1257":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-21","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"`blocked_by_preflight`"},"1258":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-22","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"The runner's preflight refused to execute (missing workflow source, auth not ready, repo path problems)."},"1259":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-23","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Check run diagnostics; fix workflow config or runner setup."},"1260":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-24","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"`provider_limited`"},"1261":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-25","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Model provider rate limit / quota / overload."},"1262":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-26","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Wait and re-run; check the provider account."},"1263":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-27","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"`timed_out`"},"1264":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-28","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"The run exceeded a deadline or an operation timed out."},"1265":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-29","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Re-run; if recurring, raise the workflow's time budget or shrink the job."},"1266":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-30","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"`invalid_output`"},"1267":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-31","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"The agent's output failed schema validation."},"1268":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-32","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Inspect logs; tighten the prompt or loosen the output schema."},"1269":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-33","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"`infra_unavailable`"},"1270":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-34","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Network/DNS/disk/spawn failures, runner offline mid-run."},"1271":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-35","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Fix the runner host; re-run."},"1272":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-36","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"`needs_human`"},"1273":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-37","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"The workflow concluded a human must act."},"1274":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-38","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Read the run output and the linked approval/escalation card."},"1275":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-39","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"`failed`"},"1276":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-40","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Unclassified failure."},"1277":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-41","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#failure-classes","content":"Start with diagnostics and logs."},"1278":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-42","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#preflight-blockers","content":"`runyard preflight <workflow>` (or `POST /api/workflows/{id}/preflight`) reports `ready`, `needs_input` (with questions — usually missing required input fields), or `blocked` with coded blockers, including:"},"1279":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-43","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#preflight-blockers","content":"`missing_secret` / `secrets_unavailable` — required secrets are not stored, or the secret store is disabled (set `SECRETS_ENC_KEY` on the Hub, then `PUT /api/secrets/{key}`)."},"1280":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-44","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#preflight-blockers","content":"`no_matching_runner` — no registered runner matches the required tags/location."},"1281":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-45","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#preflight-blockers","content":"`workflow_disabled`, `workflow_not_found` — an admin can re-enable via `PATCH /api/workflows/{id}`."},"1282":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-46","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#preflight-blockers","content":"`workflow_bundle_missing` / `workflow_source_missing` — the definition references source that is not published; send source bytes via `update_workflow`."},"1283":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-47","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#preflight-blockers","content":"`repo_dir_invalid`, `hook_blocked` — input points outside allowlisted repos, or requests hook profiles that are not enabled for the workflow."},"1284":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-48","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#401--403-responses","content":"`401` means no valid token; `403 insufficient scope` means the token lacks the required scope (the response names it). Check what you are authenticated as:"},"1285":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-49","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#401--403-responses","content":"Admin actions (creating workflows, secrets, tokens, schedules) need `admin`; running workflows needs `api` or `mcp`; the runner protocol needs `runner`. Ask a Hub admin for a token with the right scopes."},"1286":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-50","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#secrets-not-configured","content":"If secret endpoints return an error about the store being disabled, the Hub has no valid `SECRETS_ENC_KEY`. Set a 32-byte base64/hex key in the Hub env file and restart. Note that rotating an existing key makes previously stored secrets unreadable."},"1287":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-51","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#telegram-not-delivering","content":"Verify, in order: `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` and `TELEGRAM_APPROVAL_CHAT_ID` are set on the Hub; the bot's webhook points at `https://hub.example.com/api/telegram/webhook` with the matching `TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET`; the bot is a member of the target chat; and the users pressing buttons are listed in `TELEGRAM_APPROVAL_USER_IDS`. Response-endpoint deliveries record their state (`status`, `attempts`, `last_error`) on `GET /api/runs/{id}` under `responseEndpoints[]`."},"1288":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-52","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#runner-agent-auth-expired","content":"Runs failing with provider auth errors usually mean the runner's `codex`/`claude` CLI login lapsed. On hosts with `REAUTH_ENABLED=1`, an admin can trigger re-auth from the web app (runner card → Re-auth): the Hub surfaces a verification URL and user code, and never token material. Otherwise, log in on the runner host directly (`codex login`, `claude setup-token`)."},"1289":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-53","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#where-to-look-generally","content":"Surface"},"1290":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-54","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#where-to-look-generally","content":"What it tells you"},"1291":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-55","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#where-to-look-generally","content":"`GET /api/runs/{id}/diagnostics`"},"1292":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-56","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#where-to-look-generally","content":"Structured diagnosis + log summary for a run (`get_run_diagnostics`)."},"1293":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-57","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#where-to-look-generally","content":"`runyard tail <run-id>`"},"1294":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-58","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#where-to-look-generally","content":"Unified timeline: status transitions, events, artifacts as NDJSON."},"1295":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-59","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#where-to-look-generally","content":"`runyard audit`"},"1296":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-60","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#where-to-look-generally","content":"Who did what (admin)."},"1297":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-61","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#where-to-look-generally","content":"`GET /readyz`"},"1298":{"id":"/guides/troubleshooting-62","page_id":"/guides/troubleshooting","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/troubleshooting#where-to-look-generally","content":"Hub readiness — `503` means the Hub cannot serve (for example a database problem)."},"1299":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","type":"page","content":"Authoring workflows","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Guides"],"tags":[],"url":"/guides/workflows-authoring"},"1300":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-0","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring","content":"Create and edit workflows by sending source bytes over the API or MCP; the Hub stores them as immutable, versioned bundles."},"1301":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-1","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"Definition anatomy"},"1302":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-2","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#a-minimal-real-example","content":"A minimal, real example"},"1303":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-3","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#updating-a-workflow","content":"Updating a workflow"},"1304":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-4","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#moving-workflows-between-hubs-workflow-packages","content":"Moving workflows between Hubs: workflow packages"},"1305":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-5","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#the-web-editor","content":"The web editor"},"1306":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-6","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring","content":"Workflows are stored in the Hub database as immutable, versioned source bundles. You create or update a workflow by sending its definition — **including the workflow source bytes** — over HTTP (`POST /api/workflows`, `PATCH /api/workflows/{id}`) or MCP (`create_workflow` / `update_workflow`). The Hub publishes the source as a hash-addressed bundle and records its id on the definition as `workflow.bundleId`."},"1307":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-7","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring","content":"Do NOT write workflow files to disk: custom workflow definitions that reference bare `workflow.entry` file paths without source bytes are rejected (`workflow_source_required`). Repository-authored workflow files are reserved for the shipped internal/dev seed catalog only. The web app's workflow editor is not an exception — it calls these same API endpoints."},"1308":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-8","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring","content":"Both operations require an admin-scoped token."},"1309":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-9","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"Field"},"1310":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-10","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"Meaning"},"1311":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-11","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"`slug`"},"1312":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-12","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"Stable identifier used in URLs, the CLI, and MCP (`runyard run <slug>`)."},"1313":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-13","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"`name`"},"1314":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-14","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"Human-readable display name."},"1315":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-15","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"`description`"},"1316":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-16","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"What the workflow does; shown in the catalog and menus."},"1317":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-17","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"`category`"},"1318":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-18","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"Catalog grouping (for example `Examples`, `Operations`)."},"1319":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-19","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"`inputSchema`"},"1320":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-20","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"JSON Schema for run input. Required fields drive preflight questions."},"1321":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-21","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"`outputSchema`"},"1322":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-22","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"JSON Schema for the structured run output."},"1323":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-23","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"`requiredRunnerTags`"},"1324":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-24","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"Tags a runner must advertise to claim runs (for example `[\"smithers\"]`)."},"1325":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-25","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"`approvalPolicy`"},"1326":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-26","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"Whether runs hold for a human approval before executing (`{ \"required\": true }`)."},"1327":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-27","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"`workflow.engine`"},"1328":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-28","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"Execution engine; `\"smithers\"`."},"1329":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-29","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"`workflow.source`"},"1330":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-30","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"The workflow source bytes, sent inline as a string (aliases: `workflow.sourceBytes`, `workflow.code`)."},"1331":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-31","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"`workflow.language`"},"1332":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-32","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#definition-anatomy","content":"Source language, defaults to `tsx`."},"1333":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-33","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#a-minimal-real-example","content":"The source is a small Smithers TSX workflow (modeled on the seeded `hello` workflow): one task, structured output validated with Zod."},"1334":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-34","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#a-minimal-real-example","content":"Create the workflow by sending that source inline as `workflow.source` (a JSON string — the TSX above, escaped):"},"1335":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-35","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#a-minimal-real-example","content":"Over MCP the same payload goes to `create_workflow` as the `workflow` argument. The response definition carries `workflow.bundleId` instead of the inline source — the bytes now live in the Hub DB. Runners fetch the bundle at execution time; nothing needs to exist on any runner's filesystem beforehand."},"1336":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-36","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#updating-a-workflow","content":"Send the changed definition — again with source bytes inline — via `PATCH /api/workflows/{id}` or `update_workflow`. The Hub publishes a **new** bundle version and repoints `workflow.bundleId`; existing bundles are never mutated, so historical runs keep an exact record of what they executed. Identical bytes are deduplicated by hash rather than republished."},"1337":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-37","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#updating-a-workflow","content":"Inspect what is stored:"},"1338":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-38","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#updating-a-workflow","content":"The corresponding MCP tools are `get_workflow_source`, `list_workflow_bundles`, and `get_workflow_bundle` (which does include the source). You can also publish a bundle directly with `POST /api/workflow-bundles` / `publish_workflow_bundle` and reference it by `workflow.bundleId`, but prefer inline source — the Hub publishes the bundle for you."},"1339":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-39","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#moving-workflows-between-hubs-workflow-packages","content":"Admins can export a workflow as a portable `.runyard-workflow.json` package file. It contains the workflow source bytes, metadata, requirements, and content hashes — never secret values."},"1340":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-40","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#moving-workflows-between-hubs-workflow-packages","content":"Imports publish the package's source as a DB workflow bundle and install the workflow **disabled** until the receiving Hub's secrets, runners, and configuration are ready; an admin enables it with `PATCH /api/workflows/{id}`. The HTTP equivalents live under `/api/workflow-packages/*`, and MCP exposes `export_workflow_package`, `validate_workflow_package`, `preview_workflow_import`, and `import_workflow_package`."},"1341":{"id":"/guides/workflows-authoring-41","page_id":"/guides/workflows-authoring","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/workflows-authoring#the-web-editor","content":"The web app's workflow create/edit screens are ordinary clients of `POST /api/workflows` and `PATCH /api/workflows/{id}`: they submit the definition with inline source bytes and the Hub publishes the bundle, exactly as above. There is no separate, privileged authoring path."}},"count":1341},"sorting":{"language":"english","sortableProperties":["content","page_id","type","url"],"sortablePropertiesWithTypes":{"content":"string","page_id":"string","type":"string","url":"string"},"sorts":{"content":{"docs":{"1":1296,"2":539,"3":899,"4":1070,"5":1073,"6":1072,"7":501,"8":498,"9":499,"10":500,"11":982,"12":823,"13":502,"14":504,"15":505,"16":508,"17":510,"18":511,"19":1310,"20":1244,"21":1197,"22":1282,"23":1216,"24":915,"25":920,"26":716,"27":828,"28":1058,"29":811,"30":1249,"31":427,"32":284,"33":1292,"34":669,"35":863,"36":1212,"37":632,"38":616,"39":582,"40":583,"41":1219,"42":1226,"43":797,"44":1315,"45":594,"46":586,"47":655,"48":1299,"49":26,"50":1018,"51":66,"52":895,"53":41,"54":1000,"55":585,"56":544,"57":988,"58":814,"59":726,"60":867,"61":905,"62":185,"63":296,"64":344,"65":155,"66":557,"67":333,"68":478,"69":558,"70":233,"71":314,"72":382,"73":159,"74":559,"75":337,"76":481,"77":560,"78":199,"79":453,"80":90,"81":361,"82":157,"83":561,"84":334,"85":479,"86":562,"87":612,"88":606,"89":842,"90":1160,"91":1125,"92":1247,"93":938,"94":595,"95":587,"96":839,"97":1300,"98":492,"99":545,"100":178,"101":633,"102":457,"103":525,"104":163,"105":593,"106":1171