n each card's `context`, alongside the ask, the linked run, and deep links."],[192,"The API hands these links back so agents and integrations can point humans at the right screen without building URLs themselves:"],[676,"The API-first guarantee"],[90,"The ask contract"],[1020,"The bootstrap script installs these for you, retargeted to your install\ndirectory, env-file location, and node binary. Secrets live in the\n`EnvironmentFile`s (mode `0600`), never in the units."],[926,"The bot's API token."],[219,"The caller selects profiles per run with `input.postRunHooks: [\"publish-docs\", …]`."],[331,"The caller's execution intent: `executionMode: \"local\" | \"remote\" | \"auto\"` (optionally a specific `runnerLocation`). `remote` targets the shared remote/VPS pool (default location `vps`); `auto` takes any matching runner."],[252,"The catalog"],[595,"The catalog unit of Runyard - versioned definitions with schemas, immutable source bundles, and portable packages."],[954,"The CLI stores named remotes (Hub URL + token) in `~/.runyard/config.json`\n(mode `0600`). Every command accepts global options `--url`, `--token`,\n`--remote <name>`, and `--json` (machine-readable output)."],[295,"The CLI takes budgets as flags: `runyard run research --max-tokens 200000 --max-cost 2` (`--max-cost` is US dollars; the same flags work on `runyard preflight`)."],[693,"The complete MCP tool set (parity-tested against the API surface). Connect with `runyard mcp install` or the `runyard-mcp` stdio server."],[1338,"The corresponding MCP tools are `get_workflow_source`, `list_workflow_bundles`, and `get_workflow_bundle` (which does include the source). You can also publish a bundle directly with `POST /api/workflow-bundles` / `publish_workflow_bundle` and reference it by `workflow.bundleId`, but prefer inline source — the Hub publishes the bundle for you."],[106,"The creator of a card states the ask up front, and every surface renders it verbatim:"],[1096,"The current saved remote"],[904,"The